Since living independently, I've enjoyed getting rid of all the unnecessary stuff around me. Everyone has their idea of what an ideal life looks like. For me, stripping away the things I don't need leaves me with my ideal life. So, after graduating with my master's, I set off on a 41-day journey from Kochi, a rural part of Japan, with my bike and some simple camping gear, heading towards Tokyo.

